Second largest shark, but suprisenly it only eats plankton. These sharks usually grow to 26-33ft and can open their mouth about 3ft. They are found in all the temperate oceans. They swim with their mouths open during feeding time and use something called gill rakers to filter through the large amount of water for plankton, they also have about 100 teeth per row. They swim 660ft below the surface but during winter they go down to 3000ft.
